Gijima, Sasol, Standard Bank May Move: South African Stock Market Preview

-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 
2011-02-25T05:44:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/gijima-sasol-standard-bank-south-african-stock-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.    South Africa ’s FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index weakened for
a third day, falling 225.6, or 0.7 percent, to 31,706.47 at the
5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.    Gijima Group Ltd . (GIJ SJ): The information technology
company said it’s optimistic it will resolve a dispute with the
Department of Home Affairs regarding the validity of a contract.
Shares in were unchanged at 78 cents.  Sasol Ltd. (SOL SJ): Oil climbed to the highest level in 29
months yesterday as Libya’s uprising reduced supplies from
Africa’s third-biggest oil-producer. Sasol, the world’s largest
maker of motor and jet fuel from coal, gained 7.45 rand, or 2
percent, to 381.25 rand.  Standard Bank Group Ltd. (SBK SJ): South African Finance
Minister  Pravin Gordhan  analyzes the upcoming year’s budget and
may comment on inflation and banking regulation. Shares in  Standard Bank  fell 80 cents, or 0.8 percent, to 98.70 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) rose 2 percent to $25.64.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) declined 0.7 percent to $48.24.
BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) lost 0.6 percent to $76.29. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) fell 4.9 percent to $4.63. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) slid 2.2 percent to $17.26. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY US)
added 0.7 percent to $11.63. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY US)
lost 1 percent to $28.75. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) retreated 0.6
percent $5.06.  Sasol Ltd . (SSL US) gained 2.5 percent to $54.21.  To contact the reporter on this story:
